1
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:48,965
Okay, so you think Chiara
can betray Mikoy?

2
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:50,717
<i>She will never do that.</i>

3
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,887
<i>Her dream is to be free.</i>

4
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:55,889
Agent Alex, you were a witness.

5
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,474
<i>You saw how she left everything behind.</i>

6
00:00:57,557 --> 00:01:00,268
<i>Family and name.</i>

7
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:02,479
What I'm holding on to
is that she loves me.

8
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:03,688
<i>And that's what she chose.</i>

9
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:24,250
<i>What you are asking from me</i>

10
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:28,254
<i>is to allow Chiara to reconnect</i>
<i>with the same</i>

11
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:33,635
criminal organization that raised her,
trained her, protected her,

12
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:35,762
manipulated her.

13
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,161
How was the meeting last night?

14
00:02:00,745 --> 00:02:03,665
Should we say congratulations
or condolences?

15
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:05,333
‪All right.

16
00:02:06,042 --> 00:02:07,585
Sweetheart, this is for you.

17
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:33,111
Chiara, I listened.

18
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:38,533
Because I said I'd try.

19
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,995
And I know you're thinking
that you can control it.

20
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:45,123
But it's our job
to think about what if you can't.

21
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,917
What if Chiara is right?

22
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,545
If Viktor, Uncle Vik,

23
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:53,006
still cares, right?

24
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:56,009
The risk is too high.

25
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:59,470
Not because I think you're weak.

26
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:02,015
Not because I think you're a traitor.

27
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:04,517
But sometimes, no matter how good you are,

28
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:08,771
there are just people it's hard
to be objective about, especially family.

29
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:12,984
It's not personal, but even if
I want to trust you,

30
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,945
we can't base our decision
on feelings alone.

31
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:22,076
But there's a compromise.

32
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,091
We just need the people upstairs
to approve it.

33
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,735
Angelito. How many girls do you have now?

34
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:56,945
Oh, none!

35
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:59,697
What do you mean none? You've got two!

36
00:04:00,281 --> 00:04:01,783
Two? More like three!

37
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:06,079
Angelito told me they're just friends,
just friendship.

38
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:07,705
Just let him be.

39
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,041
But on another note, Mr. Mario,

40
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:13,836
I've noticed vehicles driving around here.

41
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,923
Motorcycles too, like
those riding-in-tandem guys.

42
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:20,009
Actually even people, watching
this place and circling around.

43
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,719
I have a bad feeling about it.

44
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,182
Actually, Dad, yes.

45
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,893
Some people suddenly
came around doing a census.

46
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:33,106
And then there's also
a helicopter circling around.

47
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:39,404
Guys, let's not panic.

48
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:42,156
But of course, let's be extra careful.

49
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:45,868
Don't worry, Mr. Mario, I'll handle it.

50
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,663
I'll double our security.

51
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:50,832
I'll add more people
who look like this guy.

52
00:04:53,501 --> 00:04:55,545
Thank you very much, Captain Pepe.

53
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:58,631
So what now? Guys, gossipers,

54
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,508
come here.

55
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:03,845
Come here.

56
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:06,556
Go find more people who look like you.

57
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:09,809
All right, Captain Pepe, I'll go look.

58
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:11,060
All right, hurry up.

59
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,437
He looks like his cousin.

60
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,106
As many as you can,
as long as they look like you.

61
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:37,712
Is she okay?

62
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:40,882
Maybe she's stressed?

63
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:43,801
Trying to release stress?

64
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:46,596
Oh?

65
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:48,556
Yes.

66
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:52,310
Usually, she just sleeps or walks around.

67
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:55,313
You know, to lower cortisol, apparently.

68
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,024
Maybe she needs a spa day,

69
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,193
something relaxing.

70
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:03,738
They said Shamrock Spa is good.

71
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:07,950
You know, actually, this is the first time
I've seen her like this.

72
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:49,700
So hardworking!

73
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:56,499
That's how it is.
When things feel messy inside,

74
00:06:57,125 --> 00:07:00,211
it feels good to clean up out here.
It's a stress reliever.

75
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:07,218
Are you okay?

76
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,929
Actually, no.

77
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:12,682
I didn't bring my personal pillow.

78
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:16,686
The pillows here are so soft
that I think I got a stiff neck.

79
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:22,483
Or maybe it's just tension.

80
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,736
Cause ever since we got here,
everyone seems tired.

81
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:28,906
Like everyone's carrying
something heavy inside.

82
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:50,136
You know, I miss it.

83
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:54,515
When we still had family dinners,

84
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:58,102
stories, laughter.

85
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:02,648
Oh, well.

86
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,449
Yes. You're actually really good.

87
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,493
It's so relaxing, it makes me sleepy.

88
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:16,662
My stiff neck is gone. Amazing!

89
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:19,665
Now I know why Mikoy
is so in love with you.

90
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:21,792
You're amazing, all right.

91
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:23,836
I'm gonna take a nap first.

92
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,254
Wow, you're incredible!

93
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,716
I feel like I just got a massage
from a thousand fairies!

94
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:31,010
It really feels good.

95
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,409
Are you okay?

96
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:56,846
Are you planning something?

97
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:29,837
Mikoy.

98
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,551
I want to talk to Dad.

99
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:39,263
I need to talk to Dad.

100
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,353
I know the agency doesn't want this,

101
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:49,065
and I know it's dangerous,
and I know they have a point.

102
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:54,403
But if I have to tell them
every decision I'm going to make,

103
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,905
how am I supposed to move?

104
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,910
How am I supposed to protect Mom and Dad?

105
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:05,164
How am I supposed to protect everyone
we want to go back to after this?

106
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,669
And if it's true that
La Morte Bianca is really here…

107
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:15,466
then I really need to talk to Dad.

108
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:24,410
<i>The problem with these weapons is,</i>

109
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:29,748
<i>you can't undo the damage they can cause.</i>

110
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,917
<i>One wrong decision.</i>

111
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:33,794
<i>One wrong person.</i>

112
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:36,297
<i>One wrong day.</i>

113
00:12:37,047 --> 00:12:41,093
<i>Sometimes that's enough</i>
<i>to change the world.</i>

114
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,684
<i>To protect everyone's safety,</i>

115
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:51,937
<i>to make sure no one can use it,</i>

116
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:53,689
<i>we need to get to them first.</i>

117
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,568
John, Maki!

118
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:58,694
Let's just switch places.

119
00:12:58,777 --> 00:13:01,780
You do the rounds,
then we'll take the post.

120
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:02,740
- Copy.
- Where are we?

121
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,533
You, Maki, go over there.

122
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:05,910
You, John, go over there.

123
00:13:10,706 --> 00:13:11,665
Deaf.

124
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:15,711
Captain Pepe.

125
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:18,255
You should do the rounds.
You look tired already.

126
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:19,632
All right, where are we?

127
00:13:19,715 --> 00:13:21,926
- You go there, and he goes there.
- Okay.

128
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:23,093
All right, okay.

129
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,140
He's really deaf.

130
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:31,977
<i>Cook, cook, cook</i>

131
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:33,979
<i>I'm cooking</i>

132
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:34,897
<i>Yes, yes, yes</i>

133
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:37,066
<i>I'm really getting good</i>

134
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:38,943
<i>At cooking so well</i>

135
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:43,072
<i>They'll all fall in love</i>
<i>Charmed by a dash of pepper</i>

136
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,615
<i>L-O-V-E, na na na</i>

137
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,200
<i>So delicious, ha ha ha!</i>

138
00:13:46,283 --> 00:13:47,660
<i>I'm gonna eat you up!</i>

139
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:49,745
<i>Coming right up, coming right up!</i>

140
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:55,334
<i>Do you want to taste my cooking?</i>

141
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:56,961
<i>Coming right up, coming right up!</i>

142
00:13:57,044 --> 00:13:58,504
<i>Here it is!</i>

143
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,048
- This is so good, bro!
- Your cooking is so good!

144
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:04,718
Delicious!

145
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:07,096
Nice, a special dinner!

146
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,514
Wait, what did you eat?

147
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,432
Wow, why are you
in such a good mood today?

148
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:13,894
Bro, I had the best sleep of my life
because of your sweetheart.

149
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:16,230
Now I get why you're in love with her.

150
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:19,859
Just think about her hands.
They're so deadly!

151
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:23,529
But also therapeutic
and healing at the same time.

152
00:14:23,612 --> 00:14:25,072
I slept so well when she pressed on me,

153
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:27,032
my stiff neck disappeared.

154
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,743
<i>Knock, knock, knock, I'm cooking!</i>

155
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:32,288
<i>Yes, yes, yes, you're really handsome</i>

156
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:33,414
Oh, me?!

157
00:14:33,497 --> 00:14:34,915
<i>L-O-V-E, na, na, na</i>

158
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,876
<i>I'm cooking</i>

159
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:40,170
- <i>Yes, yes, yes, you're really amazing</i>
- Yes!

160
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:43,424
<i>We're handsome if we eat this!</i>

161
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:45,926
So, what?

162
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:46,969
Is it final?

163
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,220
The beach?

164
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:52,016
Then camping!

165
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:56,061
And content!

166
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:57,187
- All right.
- All right.

167
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:58,522
And exhaustion?

168
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,440
Ouch.

169
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:00,774
Go ahead and do all that,

170
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,985
so you can really enjoy your vacation.

171
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:05,487
But be careful, okay?

172
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:06,780
Yes, Dad.

173
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:10,284
What a shame, the staff
will be one person short.

174
00:15:10,367 --> 00:15:12,411
Come on. It's fine.

175
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:16,498
What's important is no one swims too far.

176
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,667
No one goes missing.

177
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:20,252
And please,

178
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:23,756
don't fool around inside the boat, okay?

179
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:25,633
There's more, okay?

180
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:29,136
Charge your phones, bring water,

181
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:31,305
let us know… What else?

182
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:32,264
Text us.

183
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:33,223
- There.
- Yes.

184
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:35,100
Okay, text us where you are.

185
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:36,560
Yes, Dad.

186
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:39,104
And wear sunscreen.

187
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,981
You really had to slip that in, huh?

188
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:44,151
Amazing!

189
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:46,278
- Nice one.
- Let's eat.

190
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:48,489
- That's enough.
- Come on, let's eat.

191
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,077
- <i>Let's eat, baby.</i>
- <i>Let's eat, baby.</i>

192
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,912
<i>La-la-la love, la-la-la love</i>

193
00:15:54,995 --> 00:15:57,247
- <i>We cooked this, baby</i>
- <i>We cooked this, baby</i>

194
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:59,166
<i>La-la-la love, la-la-la love</i>

195
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:01,001
<i>This tinola is so good</i>

196
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:03,003
<i>La-la-la love, la-la-la love</i>

197
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,880
<i>Mikoy helped me</i>

198
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,132
<i>La-la-la love, la-la-la love</i>

199
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:19,812
Is this witness protection
or a restaurant grand opening?

200
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:20,896
Oh, Alex.

201
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:24,149
We deserve the finer things
in life, especially you, right?

202
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:40,666
Hey, let's go. They're here.

203
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:44,712
What are you doing here?

204
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:46,213
Huh?

205
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:51,593
- We even brought dessert.
- Yup!

206
00:16:53,303 --> 00:16:54,346
Shrimp fritters?

207
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:05,607
There's effort. There are candles.

208
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,276
There's L-O-V-E.

209
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:10,279
- Solid!
- Of course!

210
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,239
There's no rat in his head.

211
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:17,536
Ratatouille.

212
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:23,167
Come on, let's eat.

213
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,169
- Come on, come on! Sit, sit.
- Try it!

214
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:26,420
I'll just get a plate.

215
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:27,629
Sit.

216
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:29,381
Thanks, Cocoy!

217
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:30,758
He can handle it.

218
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:36,680
That looks good.

219
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,184
Sorry, I forgot we have guests.

220
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:42,394
You know what?

221
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:45,022
It's perfect because
we're all complete today.

222
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:47,524
Of course, I want to contribute too.

223
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,819
What am I good at?

224
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,160
Oh, that's something you should all try!

225
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:00,370
You know, earlier, I had a stiff neck.

226
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:03,749
I seriously couldn't move.
I was so stressed, so miserable.

227
00:18:04,374 --> 00:18:06,251
Chiara's hands are something else, deadly,

228
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:07,753
but who would've thought

229
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:11,131
they also have healing properties
and are relaxing too.

230
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:13,175
Didn't everything go away?

231
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,680
Because I'm sure,
especially for the agents,

232
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:20,432
you're even more stressed.

233
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,230
- Eat, massage?
- Eat, massage?

234
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:27,189
- Sleep!
- All right.

235
00:18:27,272 --> 00:18:29,024
We're getting a massage too, right?

236
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:31,110
Massage? That would be nice!

237
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:33,028
It's just perfect.

238
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:35,823
And Dara and I even brought dessert.

239
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:37,199
Then straight to sleep, right?
Sounds good.

240
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:38,575
Here, this is cassava cake.

241
00:19:42,055 --> 00:19:43,265
What happened?

242
00:19:47,227 --> 00:19:50,772
Wow, I slept for so long.

243
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:53,859
You know that feeling when it's like
I dreamed eight times,

244
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:57,613
then I astral projected three times.

245
00:19:57,696 --> 00:20:01,116
Look, he's sleeping so deeply!
Especially this one, dead asleep.

246
00:20:02,492 --> 00:20:03,493
Hey!

247
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,414
So noisy, quiet.

248
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:09,082
- Five more minutes, five more minutes.
- Drooling.

249
00:20:18,091 --> 00:20:19,051
Wow!

250
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,720
You guys sleep like a log!

251
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:25,057
I already opened all the windows,
and no one still woke up.

252
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,141
Why?

253
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:27,893
Why is this here?

254
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,528
Wow!

255
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:55,379
Looks like the idiot's finally relaxed.

256
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:57,547
I'm almost done anyway.

257
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:58,674
Do you want one too?

258
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,635
No need, thank you!

259
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:07,349
With all the knots
in Agent Sianong's muscles,

260
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:08,642
I'm sure you do too.

261
00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:11,186
You agents are super stressed.

262
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:17,859
And besides, you're really the one
helping Mikoy and me.

263
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:19,569
And you know,

264
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:22,322
it feels good

265
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:26,660
to know that my hands
aren't only capable of harm.

266
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:33,583
They can also help people
relax and feel good.

267
00:21:41,091 --> 00:21:43,218
It's okay, thank you!

268
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,262
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

269
00:21:45,345 --> 00:21:46,596
You deserve this.

270
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,473
No, it's okay, thank you!

271
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,537
Perfect, I have a stiff neck.

272
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,748
Really? Where?

273
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:13,832
Right around here.

274
00:22:13,915 --> 00:22:15,542
- Around here?
- Yes.

275
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,701
Did Chiara put us to sleep?

276
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:54,790
From what I know,
there are certain pressure points that,

277
00:22:54,873 --> 00:22:57,167
if you press them,
can make you fall asleep.

278
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,376
Maybe that's what happened.

279
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,087
- How?
- Weird.

280
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:02,255
Wait, where are Mikoy and Chiara?

281
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,803
Hurry, Sianong!

282
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,445
They took my car.

283
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:32,786
They took my car!

284
00:23:59,312 --> 00:24:01,148
<i>Mikoy and Chiara escaped.</i>

285
00:24:01,231 --> 00:24:03,358
Did the Moraviano get them?

286
00:24:03,441 --> 00:24:05,360
Is there extraction?

287
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:06,528
Go look for them!

288
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:08,530
<i>Before the Moraviano get them first!</i>

289
00:24:08,613 --> 00:24:11,658
<i>Before La Morte Bianca catch them!</i>

290
00:24:16,621 --> 00:24:18,123
She changed her way.

291
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:28,508
Friends!

292
00:24:28,592 --> 00:24:32,262
- Hey, come here. What happened?
- Oh, gosh, the Pinagpalas!

293
00:24:32,345 --> 00:24:38,435
Their house exploded!
Even their bakery is gone!

294
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:40,187
Why is it only the Pinagpalas?

295
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:42,689
For sure, it's not an accident.
It's planned!
